<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_4134"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4134-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4134">Full Faith and Credit  Driver's License&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/8428-4049">sobi</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Each state takes it upon itself to decide if the public has the right to travel public roads.  This is, in principle, wrong.  The roads do not belong to the state, they belong to the people.<br/><br/>We should not have to prove who we are to each state to travel roads that belong to us.<br/><br/>Why are driver's license's not given the constitutional full faith and credit among states.</div>
