<div id="Idea_4104"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4104-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4104">relax HIPPA rules, they interfere with getting things done accurately.&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/5672-4049">Greg Vanderlaan</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">HIPPA has turned out to be a nightmare. Since all employees are in fear of violating the regulations, the result is that the patient has to bring all their own records with them every time. We can't get charts from another department, so we simply ask the patient to fill out our form and write down all their information again. Instead of sharing information that has already been collected. We collect it again. The potential for error is bad. Many patients have poor memory... actually, 100% of the patients have poor memory in comparison to a database. </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_4104" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_4104', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2247&topicID=4104')">Comments (2)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_4104"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2247">Between Federal, State, and Local Governments</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=hippa">hippa</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=nightmare">nightmare</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=idiot laws">idiot laws</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=heath">heath</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=welfare">welfare</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_4104"></div>
